Dear friends who support the president, paki-explain naman yung context ng quote below (yung nasa ibaba) please.
Sa tingin ko, kung ibang abogado ang nagsabi nyan, ambilis nang dumating ng calls for disbarment
Edit: A friend below provides some context: &ldquo;He was talking about the amount of proof needed to conduct an investigation which is probable cause Lang NOT proof beyond reasonable doubt.&rdquo;

The series was a bit formulaic, and towards the end really preachy toward&rsquo;s the authors personal philosophies, but Terry Goodkind&rsquo;s Sword of Truth series always comes back to me because it codified one of life&rsquo;s most important truths:
 Wizard&rsquo;s First Rule: &ldquo;People are stupid. They will believe a lie because they want to believe it&rsquo;s true, or because they are afraid it might be true.&rdquo;
 That doesn&rsquo;t mean you&rsquo;re stupid or I&rsquo;m stupid, just that collectively, we&rsquo;re kind of dumb.
